quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  45,27,"God's is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, and on the day when the Hour shall arise on that day shall those who call it vain be losers"
  45,28,"And thou shalt see each nation kneeling, each nation summoned to its book, 'Today are ye rewarded for that which ye have done"
  45,29,"This is our Book that speaketh to you with truth; verily, we have written down what ye have done"
  45,30,"But as to those who believe and do righteous deeds their Lord will make them enter into His mercy, that is the obvious bliss"
  45,31,"And as for those who misbelieve,- were not my signs recited to you and ye were too big with pride and ye were a sinful people"
  45,32,"And when it was said, 'Verily, the promise of God is true, and the Hour there is no doubt therein;' ye said, 'We know not what the Hour is, we only suspect, and we are not sure"
  45,33,"But there shall appear to them the evils of what they have done, and that shall encompass them at which they have been mocking"
  45,34,"And it shall be said, 'Today will we forget you as ye forgat the meeting of this day of yours, and your resort shall be the fire, and ye shall have no helpers"
  45,35,"That is because ye took the signs of God for a jest and the life of this world deceived you; wherefore today ye shall not be brought forth therefrom, neither shall ye be taken back into favour"
  45,36,"God's then is the praise, the Lord of the heavens and the Lord of the earth, the Lord of the worlds"
  45,37,"His is the grandeur in the heavens and the earth, and He is the mighty and the wise"